Love is sticking by someone when no one would blame you for finding too difficult to stay... My best friend, my husband of 9 years and BF for 6 before that started dating me even though I had cancer, stuck with me for my 3rd open-heart surgery, a coma, major abdominal surgery that almost killed me 3 weeks later from a blood clot, pain med haziness, a  year and a half of fainting everyday, my almost being put on a transplant list (heart and liver together!) and countless doctor appointments and other close calls. I followed him after becoming stable (yes, it's possible after all that) across the US to move to his home city where he began pre-MS testing for his own symptoms. Even after his family began to realize that we had nothing in common and became abusive he and I stuck together. We're that couple that make others annoyed because we still seem like we're in our first year of marriage... 

I do this practice so that I can be strong physically, mentally and emotionally for the two of us. I'm proud to have overcome all these odds to spend my time with people that care about me without even having met me. (That's YOU!) And for the old and new friends I've made that treat me like family. Life is too short to feel disrespected and unloved. Valentine's Day will be my 19th anniversary for finally getting diagnosed and I'm thrilled to be here with all of you! xoxo Mimi
